# HSM collector conformance v1 — function sensor contract (no-params + buffered values).
# Format: case|action|arg1|arg2|...
# Actions:
# create_function_int_sensor|path|post_period_ms|constant   (harness callback returns `constant`)
# create_values_function_int_sum_sensor|path|post_period_ms|max_cache_size
#                                                            (harness callback sums the buffered snapshot)
# add_function_value|idx|value                               (buffers; values survive across posts)
# expect_no_new_payloads_for_ms|ms
# Contract notes:
# - The FIRST post fires immediately on Start, then every post period.
# - The values-function buffer is a SLIDING WINDOW, not a drain: each post passes a snapshot of
#   the buffered values to the callback; the buffer keeps them. Oldest values are evicted when
#   max_cache_size is exceeded. Values may be buffered before Start.
# - Cases that need an exact value use a long (inert) period and assert only the immediate
#   initial post; periodic cases assert timing-immune invariants.

function_posts_initial_value_immediately|create_collector
function_posts_initial_value_immediately|create_function_int_sensor|contract/func/initial|60000|42
function_posts_initial_value_immediately|start
function_posts_initial_value_immediately|expect_sent_count|1|5
function_posts_initial_value_immediately|expect_payload_contains|0|"Type":1,
function_posts_initial_value_immediately|expect_payload_contains|0|"Value":42
function_posts_initial_value_immediately|expect_no_new_payloads_for_ms|300

function_posts_constant_periodically|create_collector
function_posts_constant_periodically|create_function_int_sensor|contract/func/periodic|150|42
function_posts_constant_periodically|start
function_posts_constant_periodically|expect_sent_count_between|3|1000|10
function_posts_constant_periodically|expect_all_payloads_contain|"Value":42

values_function_receives_buffered_snapshot|create_collector
